ore: Gold

other_matl:
orebody_fm:
work_type:
model: 36a: Low-sulfide Au-quartz vein
alteration: The vein and host are oxidized to depths of 30 ft (Capps, 1915). Wall-rock alteration within a few inches of the veins is intense, but seldom extends more than 10 to 12 inches beyond the quartz filling. Sericitization and carbonate alteration predominate, but there is some pyritization and in the outer parts of the alteration zone chloritization is present (Ray, 1954).

model: 36a: Low-sulfide Au-quartz vein
alteration: Wall-rock alteration within a few inches of the veins is intense, but seldom extends more than 10 to 12 inches beyond the quartz filling.
